messages.text: Are you with your new boyfriend?
Don't tell him anything I'm texting you.
I need you to listen to me.
What did you find out about Derek?
I recognized him in the photo you posted on FaceSpace.
I've met him a few times before.
Is she the girl in the photo on your desk?
You need to get out of there, Emily.
Because you're kinda freaking me out.
Are you telling me the girl at my table drinking a grande iced mocha is officially DEAD?!
It can't be her at the coffee shop.
But something strange is definitely going on and I bet you a million bucks Derek's behind it.
He never lets me see his phone.
I've never been to his house before.
I guess it is pretty suspicious.
I just thought he was a private person.
Please come back to the dorm and talk to me.
She looks like Sasha to me.
But she introduced herself as Regina.
Does Sasha have a tattoo on her wrist?
She drowned at the beach and they couldn't find her.
I know he was involved but they all thought it was an accident.
Maybe she faked the whole thing!
Look, if you don't believe I'm with Sasha, then come to the coffee shop and see for yourself.
Then we'll figure all this shit out.
OK. Fine. I'll be there soon.
I just need to go by Kate's dorm.
My mom keeps calling me saying she can't get ahold of her.
OK, Em. I'm on my way to the coffee shop.
Her roomie said she's staying with some friends.
Speaking of friends, I need to tell you something.
Derek and Sasha asked me to come meet their friends.
We just left the coffee shop.
I thought you were waiting for me.
I couldn't think of a good excuse not to go with them!
Derek already knew I'm free for the night.
You've got me all nervous and the coffee is making me jumpy.
OK. Text me when you get there.
Alright. I'm just gonna act normal.
We just got to the house.
I don't know. It's kind of isolated out here.
It's a big brick house with white columns.
It's quiet out here. Like, spooky quiet.
He and Sasha went into the kitchen to get us something to drink.
They told me to wait in the living room.
I thought you were meeting their friends?
I don't think they talk. Like at all.
You mean they are just sitting out there silently?
Yeah. Derek told me they are deeply religious.
He said I should be "tolerant of their eccentricities."
What the hell does that mean?
I don't think he'll believe me, Andrea.
I'll text you in a few.
I'm OK. These people are weird, though.
I said I needed to go to the bathroom so I could text you.
They all seem brainwashed except Derek.
Even Sasha does whatever he says.
I thought his friends didn't talk?
Derek said they were praying in the sunroom.
They all came in after that and kept asking me questions.
About the stuff I'm into, the things I like or whatever.
They're being really friendly to me.
Maybe they aren't so dangerous after all?
Cults shower their recruits with attention and praise.
They need you to feel loved so you'll come back.
I was Homecoming Queen, Andrea. I'm loved.
Yeah. You're a diva. But obviously Derek didn't realize that.
Cults like to recruit people they think are vulnerable.
How do you know so much about cults?
I had a feeling Derek was in a cult before Sasha died.
She started acting weird when she was dating him.
It's not the time for jealousy, Em.
Anyway, I did some research online.
That's how I know about cults.
But I think she was in too deep by then.
OK, well why did Derek think I needed to be love bombed?
Popularity means the whole world to you.
And you met Derek when that asshole Conner dumped you.
I don't know if these people are actually crazy or dangerous or what, but I can't stay locked in the bathroom.
I don't want them to get suspicious of me.
Or to know I'm feeding you information.
I went along with their "love bombing" or whatever.
They all keep talking about how much better off they are here.
Like I could be better off, too.
Somehow I agreed to stay the night.
I don't know. They seem kind of sweet sometimes.
I think Derek is a good guy, Andrea.
I'm just trying not to jump to conclusions.
Tell me where you are in the house.
I told them I needed to let my roomie know I wouldn't be home tonight.
I need to get back in.
I wanna see what's going on here.
I wanna find out about Sasha.
And I'm not breaking up with Derek without a good reason.
Don't let them mind control you!
OK, well if they're dangerous, what's the next step?
I looked up some stuff online.
But it seems like they've already "dangled the prize" in front of you.
Yeah. They seem so friendly and well-liked.
OK, who doesn't want to be liked, Andrea?
I get it, but you need acceptance like you need air.
That's why you tell EVERYONE you were Homecoming Queen.
Derek saw that need in you.
They got you to agree to stay over.
They have a lot of the same interests as me.
No, Emily. Derek told them what you like.
Stop. I told you I gotta get back.
I'll text you again before lights out, OK?
They have a bedtime. Lights out at 10.
You didn't text me before 10 like you said.
Derek told me to keep my phone in my purse.
He said he hates it when I'm always texting.
I think he wants me to be cut off from communication with anyone else.
I went to the bathroom again after lights out.
I wandered around and explored some.
There's a solid steel door at the end of the hall.
It's got a padlock. No window or slots for food or anything.
I put my ear up to the door and I think I heard someone crying.
Are you telling me there's some sort of prison cell in that house?!
And I think there's a girl in there, Andrea.
I need to get out of here.
Call a cab. Get back to the dorm.
I can't. There's a gate at the end of the driveway.
There's a fence all around the yard.
I thought it was a fancy rich people thing.
Like a gated community or something.
Hold on. I think someone's coming.
They brought the girl out of the cell.
She looked traumatized. Like she needs help.
She's skinny. I don't think they were feeding her in there.
You need to get out of there somehow. Before they lock you up, too!
Shut the fuck up and listen to me.
I told you I saw her, Andrea.
